            <title>[CASSANDRA-16523] Improve handling of unflushed hint files</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16523</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In some situations hint files can have a run of trailing zeros at the end - for example when hard-rebooting machines. These zeros can be safely ignored and we should avoid invoking the disk failure policy in these cases.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
